comments: Stewart (DET) establishes himself in a legal screening position in the path of Rivers (DEN) and incidental contact occurs as the offensive player fights over the screen.

Rivers (DEN) contests the shot driving shot attempt by Joseph (DET) in the paint. Some marginal arm contact occurs to Joseph's off-arm after he had taken it off of the ball and the contact does not impact the attempt.
Jokic (DEN) extends his arm into Stewart (DET) and the contact affects his rebounding position.
Bey (DET) is not in a legal guarding position when contact occurs with Jokic (DEN) during his dribble up the floor. The contact impacts Jokic's SQBR.
Hayes (DET) establishes himself in a legal screening position in the path of Rivers (DEN) and shuffles his feet backwards as he absorbs the contact on the screen.
Bey (DET) steps back with his left foot and his heel comes down out of bounds. Possession is correctly awarded to Denver.

Jokic (DEN) establishes himself in a legal screening position in the path of Hayes (DET) and grazing, incidental contact occurs to the latter when Jokic moves his arms as he turns on his roll to the basket.
Stewart (DET) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Jokic (DEN) that affects his driving shot attempt.
Reed (DEN) makes contact with Lyles (DET), who is in a legal screening position, and the contact dislodges Lyles from said legal position.
Joseph (DET) is not established in a legal screening position when he delivers contact to the front shoulder of Rivers (DEN) and affects his ability to defend the play.
Lyles (DET) commits a take foul on Morris (DEN).
